How do I handle a 429( Too Many Requests ) on a page built with cms-js-rendering? Because I can't manage the query with a try-catch.

i have this for example:  ( and consume around 1666 points, so around 300 calls for minute right? )

```export const query = `
# $email: "{{ request.query_dict.email }}"
# $offset: "{{request.query_dict.offset}}"
# $orderBy: "{{request.query_dict.orderBy}}"
query ContactQuery($email: String! = "email", $offset: Int! = 0 , $orderBy: [crm_deal_order_by]! = amount__asc) {
  HUBDB {
    conte(uniqueIdentifier: "email", uniqueIdentifierValue: $email) {
      email
    }
  }
  CRM {
    contact(uniqueIdentifier: "email", uniqueIdentifierValue: $email) {
      city
      firstname
      lastname
      associations {
        deal_collection__contact_to_deal(limit: 10, offset: $offset, orderBy: $orderBy) {
          total
          items {
            amount
            dealname
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
  }
`;```
